<h2>Table</h2>

<p>This library includes modules related to the table user interface element:</p>

<ul class="modules">
    <li><%= DOC.modules.render('Entity/Table') %></li>
</ul>

<h3>Usage</h3>

<h4>Basic Table</h4>

<p>While some frameworks automatically style the table elements, WebBlocks does not so as to not negatively affect existing websites. As such, to use the WebBlocks table style, apply the <code>.table</code> class to an element.</p>

<pre class="prettyprint">&lt;table class="table"&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;
        &lt;td&gt;&lt;!-- Row 1 Col 1 --&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
        &lt;td&gt;&lt;!-- Row 1 Col 2 --&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;
        &lt;td&gt;&lt;!-- Row 2 Col 1 --&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
        &lt;td&gt;&lt;!-- Row 2 Col 2 --&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;</pre>
<table class="table">
    <tr>
        <td>Row 1 Col 1</td>
        <td>Row 1 Col 2</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>Row 2 Col 1</td>
        <td>Row 2 Col 2</td>
    </tr>
</table>

